-- Calpers to Vote Against Murdoch Re-Election, Telegraph Says
-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 2012-10-14T09:56:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-14/calpers-to-vote-against-murdoch-re-election-telegraph-says.html
California Public Employees’
Retirement System and California State Teachers’ Retirement
System back resolution to split roles of chairman and CEO held
by  Rupert Murdoch  at  News Corp. (NWSA) , Telegraph reports, without
saying how it got the information.
* Calpers, with $237b under management, says it won’t support
re-election of Murdoch or sons James and Lachlan to News Corp.
board
* Calstrs votes against re-election of all News Corp. directors
* Calvert Investments, with $12.5b of assets, may also have
voted against re-appointing Murdoch and sons, Telegraph says
